<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.418.7629>
    bibo:endPage "103" ;
    bibo:journal "ZooKeys" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2014-06-20" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "418" ;
    dc:creator "Skvarla, Michael J.; Fisher, J. Ray; Dowling, Ashley P. G." ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "A review of Cunaxidae (Acariformes, Trombidiformes): Histories and diagnoses of subfamilies and genera, keys to world species, and some new locality records" ;
    fabio:hasPart <https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29876>, <https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29877> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29876>
    dc:description "Figures 3 - 6. a. dorsal. b. ventral. 3 3 - segmented pedipalp (Cunaxoidinae) 4 4 - segmented pedipalp (Scirulinae) 5 5 - segmented pedipalp that does not extend beyond the subcapitulum by more than the distal half of the genua (Bonziinae, Coleoscirinae, and Orangescirulinae) 6 5 - segmented pedipalp that reaches beyond the subcapitulum by at least the distal half of the genua (Cunaxinae)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29876" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29877>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Generalized schematic of cunaxid idiosomal morphology. 7 a Dorsal. 7 b Ventral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/29877" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

